Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
all_analysis_views(25.10)                            all_analysis_views(25.10)

Name
       all_analysis_views  -  Returns  a  Tcl list of all the defined analysis
       views in a design

Syntax
       all_analysis_views

       [-help]

       [-type <string>]

       Returns a Tcl list of all the defined analysis views in a design.

       You can use this command after creating analysis views using  the  cre-
       ate_analysis_view command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -type <string>
              Specifies the type of analysis views:

              * setup: Active setup views in the design.

              * hold: Active hold views in the design.

              * active: Active setup and hold views in the design.

              * dynamic: Dynamic analysis views in the design.

              * leakage: Leakage analysis views.

              * em: Electromigration (EM) analysis views.

              * inactive: Setup/hold views that are not in use.

              * all: All defined views in the design, including those that are
                currently inactive.

Examples
              * The  following  commands create analysis views missionSlow and
                missionFast:

       create_analysis_view \

         -name missionSlow \

         -constraint_mode missionSetup \

         -delay_corner dcWCCOM

       create_analysis_view \

         -name missionFast \

         -constraint_mode missionHold \

         -delay_corner dcBCCOM

              * The following command returns a list of the  defined  analysis
                views in the design:

                all_analysis_views

                The software returns the following results:

                {missionSlow missionFast}

Related Information
              * create_analysis_view

              * set_analysis_view

